The paper discusses a refinement calculus for modifying software and hardware architectures, specifically pipe and filter architectures. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL), as well as architecture (cs.AR) and distributed computing (cs.DC) due to the networking example mentioned. The use of mathematical foundations also suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
